    Yes I've gotten the 'Expired Content' once. It was a particularly racy subject, but I cannot remember what. I interpret it as GaG saying that you didn't violate the TOS, but on the other hand we don't want anyone in our community to have their sensitive little eyeballs hurt by this, so you can jerk off on it if you want to, and also we'll keep it "active" just in case someone Googles your question and we have the opportunity to make some ad cash off of it. But again, our sensitive wittle members might get triggered, so... censorship.
